---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { author } from '../data/author';

const trajectory = [
  { place: 'Paris', note: 'French-Brazilian, raised between the two.' },
  { place: 'Lausanne', note: 'MSc in Robotics, EPFL. Perception, learning, control.' },
  {
    place: 'Amsterdam',
    note: 'MIT Senseable City Lab. Urban tree morphology from LiDAR. Roboat — first engineering hire on autonomous vessels.',
  },
  {
    place: 'Rio de Janeiro',
    note: 'MIT Senseable City Lab — founding member of the Rio branch. Favela urban science: LiDAR, CFD airflow, solar exposure, environmental risk.',
  },
];
---

<PageLayout
  title="About"
  description="French-Brazilian researcher and builder. MIT Senseable Rio, founding member. Trained in robotics at EPFL; urban science at MIT Amsterdam; now research line on informal urban morphology in Rio."
  ogType="profile"
>
  <section class="page-wrap about">
    <header class="about-head">
      <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1 class="about-title">Théo Alessandro Hermann</h1>
      <p class="about-positioning">
        Researcher and builder. French-Brazilian, based in Rio. Founding member of the MIT Senseable
        City Lab — Rio branch.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="about-body">
      <div class="about-prose prose">
        <p>
          The work splits two ways. On one side, urban science: how the geometry of cities — formal
          and informal — produces climate, exposure, and risk at the pedestrian scale. The current
          research line at MIT Senseable Rio maps favela morphology with LiDAR and translates it
          into CFD airflow, solar exposure, and environmental signal.
        </p>
        <p>
          On the other side, robotics. Open-source benchmarks for vision-language-action models on
          top of HuggingFace lerobot. World-model work on the edge of where perception, action, and
          learning meet.
        </p>
        <p>
          The two halves talk to each other more than they look like they should. Both deal in
          geometry, measurement, and acting on the world. Both reward building the artifact before
          announcing the result.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="about-side">
        <section class="side-section">
          <span class="eyebrow">Trajectory</span>
          <ol class="trajectory">
            {
              trajectory.map((stop) => (
                <li>
                  <span class="trajectory-place">{stop.place}</span>
                  <span class="trajectory-note">{stop.note}</span>
                </li>
              ))
            }
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="side-section">
          <span class="eyebrow">Languages</span>
          <ul class="languages">
            {author.languages.map((lang) => <li>{lang}</li>)}
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="side-section">
          <span class="eyebrow">CV</span>
          <p class="side-line">
            <a href="/resume.pdf">Download CV (PDF)</a>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="side-section">
          <span class="eyebrow">Contact</span>
          <p class="side-line">
            <a href={`mailto:${author.email}`}>{author.email}</a>
          </p>
        </section>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    padding-block: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem) var(--space-section);
  }
  .about-head {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  .about-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3.25rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    max-width: 18ch;
  }
  .about-positioning {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    max-width: 44ch;
  }

  .about-body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }
  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .about-body {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) 18rem;
      gap: 4rem;
    }
  }

  .about-prose p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin-bottom: 1.25em;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .about-side {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    padding-left: 0;
    border-left: 0;
  }
  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .about-side {
      border-left: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
      padding-left: 2rem;
    }
  }
  .side-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }
  .trajectory {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.85rem;
  }
  .trajectory li {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.15rem;
    padding-left: 0.75rem;
    border-left: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
  }
  .trajectory-place {
    font-family: var(--font-cartesian);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
  .trajectory-note {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .languages {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.15rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .side-line {
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .side-line a {
    color: var(--color-ink);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    transition:
      border-color 200ms ease,
      color 200ms ease;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .side-line a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border-bottom-color: var(--color-accent);
  }
</style>
